properties.areaDesc: North Coast; Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca; Western Strait of Juan De Fuca
properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 15 at 4:12PM PST until January 15 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy wet snow continued. Additional snow accumulations 1
to 3 inches. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca lowlands, including
Port Angeles, Sequim, and Blyn, Western Strait of Juan de Fuca
lowlands, including Sekiu, Clallam Bay, and Joyce and North
coast, including Neah Bay, Forks, and Queets.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM PST THIS EVENING
